{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"Ledger's synced — `sync origin: fetched+merged, pushed`. The held-back conversations are now on origin, and the 9 fingerprints are allowlisted so they won't re-block.\n\nNow, your theory question — you've got it essentially right, and the distinction you're drawing is the important one:\n\n**Yes, the redaction path is loop-prone in a way the allowlist path isn't.** Allowlisting is *fingerprint-global*: allow it once and that value never blocks again, anywhere, including in the turns this session generates. Redaction is *per-event*: `cledger redact` scrubs event X and keeps its id stable, but it does nothing to prevent the *same raw value* from being re-captured into a **new** event — namely the transcript of the very chat where you're doing the fixing. So the dumb-combo loop is:\n\n1. Real secret S blocks sync.\n2. Human opens a fresh chat; LLM reads event X, pulling raw S into context (and thus into this session's captured transcript).\n3. LLM redacts X. But this session is now captured as new events containing S.\n4. Sync → scan flags the new events → block. Go to 1.\n\nEach turn of the crank scrubs one event and mints another. In theory, unbounded.\n\n**But it only bites in a specific gap, and several things break it:**\n\n- **The capture/scan-tier gap is the whole loop surface.** Every captured event first goes through *capture-tier* redaction. If capture-tier catches S (most real, well-formed secrets — API keys, tokens), S is placeholdered on the way *in*, the new events never contain raw S, and the loop self-heals immediately. The loop only survives for values that capture-tier **misses but scan-tier catches** — exactly the conservative-vs-broad gap. So \"a real secret\" of a recognized shape usually won't loop; a weird one that only the broad scan sees can.\n\n- **The LLM loading the raw value is the fuel.** Note it's not \"displaying\" it in prose that matters — merely *reading* the event (a `cledger show` / note read) drops raw S into a tool_result, which gets captured as a turn. To not feed the loop, the assistant has to work **only from hashes/fingerprints and never load full content** — which is what I did after the classifier blocked my value-extracting script. A competent assistant starves the loop; a dumb one refuels it every turn. Your \"dumb enough human & LLM combo\" qualifier is exactly the necessary condition.\n\n- **Human overrides** short-circuit it regardless: `cledger sync --no-scan`, or turning capture off for the repo/session, or just doing it without an LLM transcript being captured at all.\n\n**The clean structural fix** is the same one I flagged earlier, and this is the strongest argument for it: make capture-tier coverage a **superset** of scan-tier (anything that would *block* a sync must also be *redacted at capture*). If nothing scan-blockable can ever be captured raw, the loop is impossible by construction — no discipline required from whatever human/LLM is driving. The cheap version: feed the allowlist/known-secret fingerprints back into capture-time redaction so known values are scrubbed on ingest. Want me to write that up as a roadmap bullet (and maybe an issue) in the repo?","type":"text"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"3f7c4bdebc79edb30a48cb52195f7beef788c465","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","seq":232},"id":"ev1-042d29ba9cdd2ba34b3666af5f7f38e02bdd3ae9821532f6e2dedf7f7b9fd530","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T18:54:01.228Z","producer":{"session_id":"b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.6.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","effort":"high","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message